 their home during the stay-at-home order by the Government,\u201d the statement had quoted Adesina as saying.    However, the presidential aide, said the supposed approval by the President was concocted by those he described as \u201dfake news peddlers.\u201d    Adesina, on his official Twitter handle on Saturday, said: \u201cFake news peddlers have concocted a statement, purportedly issued by me, saying FG will pay N30,000 to each Nigerian with BVN, to help them stock up before an impending national lockdown. Not me.    \u201dThe so-called statement is hereby disclaimed.\u201d    Meanwhile, the number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria as it stands is 89, according to NCDC.    &nbsp;","keywords":"buhari, Coronavirus, ","name":"Coronavirus: Presidency clarifies report of Buhari approving N30,000 relief package to Nigerians","thumbnailUrl":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/Buhari-at-the-villa-150x150.jpg","wordCount":"225","timeRequired":"60","mainEntity":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/2020\/03\/28\/coronavirus-presidency-clarifies-report-of-buhari-approving-n30000-relief-package-to-nigerians\/"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Don Silas","description":"","url":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/author\/don-silas\/","sameAs":[],"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/7e5ab1a5a998f33fc8d72f29ed5dd175?s=96&d=mm&r=g","height":96,"width":96}},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Daily Post Nigeria","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/DailyPost_Logo_Nov_2014_160x50.jpg","width":"158","height":"50"}},"image":[{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/2020\/03\/28\/coronavirus-presidency-clarifies-report-of-buhari-approving-n30000-relief-package-to-nigerians\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\/\/dailypost.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/Buhari-at-the-villa.jpg","width":"1200","height":"675"}]}]
